    },
    {
      "type": "group",
      "id": "grp_pipeline_ts01",
      "x": -560,
      "y": -120,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 500,
      "color": "6",
      "label": "PIPELINE DEFINITION"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "s3c4d5e6f7g8h9i0",
      "x": -340,
      "y": 540,
      "width": 480,
      "height": 460,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "## Step (atomic unit)\n\n```ts\ninterface Step {\n  kind: \"step\";\n  label: string;\n  model?: ModelId;     // \"sonnet\"|\"flash\"|\"haiku\"|\"opus\"\n  tools?: string[];    // e.g. [\"bash\", \"read\"]\n  temperature?: number;\n  systemPrompt?: string;\n  skills?: string[];\n  prompt: string;      // supports $INPUT, $ORIGINAL\n  gate?: Gate;\n  onFail?: OnFail;\n  transform: Transform;\n}\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "pip01a2b3c4d5e6f7",
      "x": -540,
      "y": -80,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 440,
      "color": "6",
      "text": "## 📦 pipeline.ts\n\nExport any `Runnable` — fully type-safe\n\n```ts\nimport { retry, skip } from \"./gates/on-fail.js\";\nimport { command } from \"./gates/presets.js\";\nimport { concat, vote } from \"./merge.js\";\nimport { full } from \"./transforms/presets.js\";\n\nexport const pipeline: Parallel = {\n  kind: \"parallel\",\n  steps: [researchStep, analyzeStep],\n  merge: vote,\n  gate: command(\"bun test\"),\n  onFail: retry(2),\n  transform: full,\n};\n```\n\nLoad with: `captain load <path>`"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "pre01b2c3d4e5f6g7",
      "x": -100,
      "y": -80,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 440,
      "color": "6",
      "text": "## 🔧 Built-in Presets\n\n**Gates** (`gates/presets.ts`)\n`command(cmd)` — exit 0 passes\n`file(path)` — file must exist\n`regex(pat)` — output matches\n`allOf(...gates)`, `anyOf(...gates)`\n`llm(prompt)`, `llmFast(prompt)`\n\n**OnFail** (`gates/on-fail.ts`)\n`retry(max?)`, `retryWithDelay(max, ms)`\n`fallback(step)`, `skip`, `warn`\n\n**Transforms** (`transforms/presets.ts`)\n`full`, `extract(key)`, `summarize()`\n\n**Merge** (`merge.ts`)\n`concat`, `awaitAll`, `rank`, `vote`, `firstPass`"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "p8h9i0j1k2l3m4n5",
      "x": -780,
      "y": 1350,
      "width": 150,
      "height": 55,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**step: plan**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "d0j1k2l3m4n5o6p7",
      "x": -780,
      "y": 1420,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 300,
      "text": "Steps run in order\nOutput chains via `$INPUT`\n\n```ts\nconst seq: Sequential = {\n  kind: \"sequential\",\n  steps: [planStep, buildStep],\n};\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "b9i0j1k2l3m4n5o6",
      "x": -610,
      "y": 1350,
      "width": 150,
      "height": 55,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**step: build**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "f2l3m4n5o6p7q8r9",
      "x": -250,
      "y": 1350,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 55,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**step: search** × 5"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "m3m4n5o6p7q8r9s0",
      "x": -250,
      "y": 1420,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 310,
      "text": "Replicate **one** step N times\nSame type, different inputs\n\n```ts\nconst p: Pool = {\n  kind: \"pool\",\n  step: searchStep,\n  count: 5,\n  merge: vote,\n};\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "e5o6p7q8r9s0t1u2",
      "x": 280,
      "y": 1350,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 55,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**search** + **lint** + **typecheck**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "h6p7q8r9s0t1u2v3",
      "x": 280,
      "y": 1420,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 310,
      "text": "Run **different** steps concurrently\nEach has its own prompt & gate\n\n```ts\nconst par: Parallel = {\n  kind: \"parallel\",\n  steps: [search, lint, typecheck],\n  merge: awaitAll,\n};\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "wt01a2b3c4d5e6f7",
      "x": 860,
      "y": 1280,
      "width": 480,
      "height": 500,
      "color": "3",
      "text": "## 🌲 Worktree Isolation Rule\n\nEvery **parallel boundary** automatically creates\na git worktree — no config needed.\n\n```ts\n// Derived path — zero config\n// .worktrees/{pipeline}-{branch}-{hash}\ntype WorktreePath = string;\n```\n\n**The rule is simple:**\n- `parallel` or `pool` → each branch gets its own worktree\n- `sequential` steps *inside* a parallel share that worktree\n- `sequential` steps *outside* parallel → main tree\n- Nested parallel → nested worktrees\n\n**parallel = worktree, always.**\nZero configuration. The topology *is* the isolation model."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "wt02b3c4d5e6f7g8",
      "x": 860,
      "y": 1820,
      "width": 480,
      "height": 520,
      "color": "3",
      "text": "## Merge Step (main tree)\n\nAfter parallel completes, merge runs on **main tree**:\n\n```ts\nconst mergeStep: Step = {\n  kind: \"step\",\n  label: \"merge\",\n  prompt: (ctx) =>\n    `${ctx.$INPUT}\\n${ctx.$ORIGINAL}`,\n  gate: command(\"git diff --check && bun test\"),\n  onFail: retry(3),\n  transform: full,\n};\n```\n\nReads worktree diffs → resolves conflicts →\nvalidated by gate → pipeline continues on main tree.\n**Just a regular step.** No special merge machinery."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "g5e6f7g8h9i0j1k2",
      "x": 420,
      "y": 390,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 590,
      "text": "## Gate & Function Types\n\n```ts\n// Gate — pure function\ntype Gate = (params: {\n  output: string;\n  ctx?: GateCtx;\n}) => true | string | Promise<true | string>;\n// true = pass, string = failure reason\n\n// OnFail — pure function\ntype OnFail = (ctx: OnFailCtx) =>\n  OnFailResult | Promise<OnFailResult>;\n\ntype OnFailResult =\n  | { action: \"retry\" }\n  | { action: \"fail\" }\n  | { action: \"skip\" }\n  | { action: \"warn\" }\n  | { action: \"fallback\"; step: Step };\n\n// Transform — pure function\ntype Transform = (params: {\n  output: string;\n  original: string;\n  ctx: TransformCtx;\n}) => string | Promise<string>;\n\n// MergeFn — pure function\ntype MergeFn = (\n  outputs: string[],\n  ctx: MergeCtx,\n) => string | Promise<string>;\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "ty01a2b3c4d5e6f7",
      "x": -1125,
      "y": 400,
      "width": 420,
      "height": 700,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "## Core Type Union\n\n```ts\n// Every composable unit is a Runnable\ntype Runnable =\n  | Step\n  | Sequential\n  | Pool\n  | Parallel;\n\ninterface Sequential {\n  kind: \"sequential\";\n  steps: Runnable[];\n  gate?: Gate;\n  onFail?: OnFail;\n  transform?: Transform;\n}\n\ninterface Pool {\n  kind: \"pool\";\n  step: Runnable;\n  count: number;\n  merge: MergeFn;\n  gate?: Gate;\n  onFail?: OnFail;\n  transform?: Transform;\n}\n\ninterface Parallel {\n  kind: \"parallel\";\n  steps: Runnable[];\n  merge: MergeFn;\n  gate?: Gate;\n  onFail?: OnFail;\n  transform?: Transform;\n}\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "t1a2b3c4d5e6f7g8",
      "x": -340,
      "y": -460,
      "width": 500,
      "height": 130,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "# Agent Orchestration\n\nComposable steps → groups → pipelines\n**Fully type-safe — TypeScript all the way down**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx12l3m4n5o6p7q8",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 2240,
      "width": 700,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "```ts\n// Recursive composition — type-safe nesting\nconst pipeline: Parallel = {\n  kind: \"parallel\",\n  steps: [\n    { kind: \"parallel\", steps: [search, analyze],\n      merge: awaitAll },\n    { kind: \"sequential\", steps: [\n      { kind: \"pool\", step: planBuild, count: 3,\n        merge: rank },\n      reviewStep,\n    ]},\n  ],\n  merge: awaitAll,\n};\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx02b3c4d5e6f7g8",
      "x": -380,
      "y": 2440,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 100,
      "text": "Any slot that accepts a **step**\nalso accepts **sequential**, **pool**,\nor **parallel** → infinite nesting"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx06f7g8h9i0j1k2",
      "x": -500,
      "y": 1955,
      "width": 240,
      "height": 45,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**step: analyze**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx05e6f7g8h9i0j1",
      "x": -760,
      "y": 1955,
      "width": 240,
      "height": 45,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**step: search**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx07g8h9i0j1k2l3",
      "x": -760,
      "y": 2010,
      "width": 500,
      "height": 50,
      "text": "↑ 2 different steps run concurrently"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx09i0j1k2l3m4n5",
      "x": 160,
      "y": 1955,
      "width": 240,
      "height": 45,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**plan-build** × 3"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx11k2l3m4n5o6p7",
      "x": 160,
      "y": 2010,
      "width": 325,
      "height": 50,
      "text": "↑ same group replicated 3 times"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx10j1k2l3m4n5o6",
      "x": 420,
      "y": 1955,
      "width": 240,
      "height": 45,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**plan-build** × 3"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "4077fa3c90085853",
      "x": 325,
      "y": 2140,
      "width": 150,
      "height": 55,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**step: review**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "cg01a2b3c4d5e6f7",
      "x": -1660,
      "y": 900,
      "width": 420,
      "height": 340,
      "color": "3",
      "text": "## 🚦 Composition Gates\n\nGates validate the **scope** they're on:\n- `sequential.gate` → validates final chained output\n- `pool.gate` → validates merged output\n- `parallel.gate` → validates merged output\n\n**retry = retry that scope**\nThe topology is the retry boundary.\n\nNo new types — same `Gate` + `OnFail`,\njust optional on composition nodes."
    }
  ],
